            <h1>Project Overview</h1>
            <h3><p>
              For the Single Board Microcontroller challenge, I chose to work with the CanaKit Raspberry Pi 3 Model B. The Raspberry Pi is described as “a low cost, credit-card sized computer that plugs into a computer monitor or TV and uses a standard keyboard and mouse.” (Raspberry Pi Foundation, n.d.-b, para. 1) Raspberry Pi is a tiny computer, with the abilities to carry out the same tasks as a laptop or desktop computer.
            </p></h3>
