            </div>
            <div ng-click="showme2= !showme2">
              <div class="row" ng-show="showme2">
                <div class="col-md-8">
                  <h4><p>Using the Raspberry Pi, I wanted to create a detection system for flooding that would alert me when water was present in my basement. This corresponds to the Nebraska College and Career Ready Standards for Science:</p>
                  <br>
                  <p><em>SC.HS.5.5.E Design a solution to a complex real-world problem by breaking it down into smaller, more manageable problems that can be solved through engineering.</em></p>
                  <br>
                  <u>Objectives:</u>
                  <br>
                  <p>Content— The students will create a solution to a real-world problem.</p>
                  <br>
                  <p>Language— Using Raspberry Pi with CanaKit groups of students will create a solution to the real-world problem of home security incorporating a sensor and an alarm component.</p>
                  <br>
                  <p>Student-friendly— I can create a detections system using a sensor and an alarm to protect my house from a natural disaster or intruder.</p>

                </div>
